#Text=Wikinews Shorts : January 20 , 2012
#Text=A compilation of brief news reports for
#Text=Friday , January 20 , 2012 .
#Text=If you believe any of these stories deserves more in-depth coverage , feel free to write a full article on the issues raised .
#Text=Dissident Republicans bomb Londonderry
#Text=No injuries were suffered when two bombs were exploded in Londonderry , Northern Ireland by Republican dissidents .
#Text=A coded message was received by the police half an hour before they were detonated in streets around the city 's main shopping centre .

#Text=Police Service of Northern Ireland Superintendent Stephen Martin has described the attacks as " cowardly and callous " , and said that the city centre will remain sealed off to allow for the search for other devices and forensic evidence .
#Text=" Bombs detonate in suspected IRA attack in Londonderry " — The Telegraph , January 20 , 2012

#Text=Kodak files for bancruptcy

#Text=Eastman Kodak Co has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in order to complete its transformation from its traditional wet film business , with which it made its name , into a specialist digital printing company .
#Text=The move would allow the company to sell off assets to pay off pension liabilities and creditors .
#Text=Beth Jinks and Mary Childs .
#Text=" Kodak Bankruptcy May Shed Photography , Bet on Digital Printing " — Bloomberg , January 20 , 2012

#Text=Republican contender Newt Gingrich refutes open marriage accusations

#Text=Newt Gingrich refutes claims by his second wife , Marianne Ginther , that he demanded that they have an open marriage so that he could continue an affair with Callista Bisek , who later became his third wife .
#Text=The accusations , aired on ABC News on Thursday , come just before the Republican party 's South Carolina presidential primary .
#Text=If true , the allegations would mean Gingrich was having an affair whilst pillorying President Bill Clinton over his involvement with Monica Lewinsky .
#Text=Barney Henderson .
#Text=" US Election 2012 : Newt Gingrich 's ex-wife Marianne gives ' explosive ' interview " — The Telegraph , January 20 , 2012
#Text=Seema Mehta , John Hoeffel .
#Text=" Gingrich rips into media , then his rivals , in GOP debate " — Los Angeles Times , January 20 , 2012
#Text=Dolce & Gabbana make apology over Hong Kong photography ban
#Text=Italian luxury goods brand Dolce & Gabbana has issued an apology over its ban on Hong Kong citizens taking photographs of its shopfront in Hong Kong , even when taken from a public sidewalk .
#Text=The ban enforced by its security guards against locals but not mainland Chinese and foreigners infuriated locals , who have staged a number of protests against the retailer .

#Text=Photography from a public place of subjects normally visible from that place is legal in Hong Kong , and the local government has been condemned for not confronting Dolce & Gabbana , leaving things to protesters to bring about the apology .
#Text=" Dolce & Gabbana Apologizes for Photo Spat " — The Wall Street Journal , January 19 , 2012

#Text=Magnitude 6.1 earthquake strikes New Zealand , no damage reported
#Text=An earthquake of magnitude 6.1 struck South Island , New Zealand yesterday .
#Text=The epicenter was located off the coast about 204 kilometers west of Invercargill at a depth of 18 kilometers .
#Text=The earthquake struck late in the day local time .
#Text=No damage or injuries were reported and no alerts were issued by the Pacific Tsunami Warning Center .
#Text=An aftershock measuring 5.2 magnitude hit the area two hours later .
#Text=An earthquake measuring 6.3 magnitude hit Christchurch last year , killing over 180 people .
#Text=There may be as many as 15,000 shocks per year in New Zealand , which is on the " Ring of Fire " .
#Text=AP . " Strong earthquake strikes off New Zealand " — The Times of India , January 19 , 2012
#Text=AFP .
#Text=" 6.1-magnitude quake strikes off N Zealand " — Hindustan Times , January 19 , 2012
